Speaking at the launch of 16 Days of Activism in Limpopo, President Zuma revealed that government declared abuse against women a 'priority crime&#8217;. JOHANNESBURG President Jacob Zuma says government has declared abuse against women a 'priority crime .The president is currently speaking at the official launch of 16 Days of Activism of No Violence Against Women and Children in Limpopo. He has urged women to speak out when their rights are violated, and allow the law to take its course. Violence against women has been declared a priority crime by government. Women must not be scared to report the perpetrators to the police. President Jacob Zuma-Minister Suzan Shabangu and Premier Stan Mathabatha at the official launch of the 16 days of Activism in Limpopo. PP pic.twitter.com/5RWZkFAbCL16 days of activism for no violence against women and children campaign launch underway AT Lebowakgomo. President Zuma be main speaker. PP pic.twitter.com/myfobJqxZr(Edited by Tamsin Wort)